===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|welth}}, {{m|enm|welthe}}, {{m|enm|weolthe||happiness, prosperity}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*welþ}}, {{m|ang|*weleþu}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*waliþō||wealth}}.
Alternatively, possibly an alteration (due to similar words in {{m|enm|-th}}: compare {{m|enm|helth||health}}, {{m|enm|derth||dearth}}) of {{m|enm|wele||wealth, well-being, weal}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|wela||wealth, prosperity}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*walô||well-being, prosperity}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*wel-||good, best}}, equivalent to {{suffix|weal|th|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|weelde||wealth}}, {{cog|nds|weelde||wealth}}, {{cog|goh|welida}}, {{m|goh|welitha||wealth}}. Related also to {{cog|de|Wohl||welfare, well-being, weal}}, {{cog|da|vel||weal, welfare}}, {{cog|sv|väl||well-being, weal}}. More at {{l|en|weal}}, {{l|en|well}}.

